utils.py changes:
- added module docstring

controversial lint which could be disabled flat-out if desired.

import is forwarded.

style

Fixed up name submodule.

name.py changes:
- Added module docstring
- Added class docstrings for Name and SubPart
- renamed ty to art_type, another controversial short-name lint which 
could also be added to the list of allowed short-names in a pylintrc
- Added docstrings for various methods within this file. In my opinion, 
these docstrings for very short functions are actually nonproductive and 
harmful, creating duplicate maintenance on future code changes. I would 
suggest the addition of a docstring-min-length item in a pylintrc file 
to not require docstrings on functions below a certain number of lines 
in length (I would suggest 5 lines)
